== Sports ==
''Main article: [[Sports in Gda<U+0144>sk]]''

There are many popular professional sports teams in the Gda<U+0144>sk and Tricity area. Amateur sports are played by thousands of Gda<U+0144>sk citizens and also in schools of all levels (elementary, secondary, university).

== Politics and local government ==
''Main article: [[Politics of Gda<U+0144>sk]]''

Contemporary Gda<U+0144>sk is the capital of the Pomeranian province and is one of the major centres of economic and administrative life in Poland. Many important  agencies of the state and local government levels have their main offices here: the Provincial Administration Office, the Provincial Government, the Ministerial Agency of the State Treasury, the Agency for Consumer and Competition Protection, the National Insurance regional office, the Court of Appeal, and the High Administrative Court.

===Regional center===
[[Gda<U+0144>sk Voivodeship]] was extended in [[1999]] to include most of [[S<U+0142>upsk Voivodeship]], the western part of [[Elbl<U+0105>g Voivodeship]] and [[Chojnice County]] from [[Bydgoszcz Voivodeship]] to form the new [[Pomeranian Voivodeship]].   
The area of the region was thus extended from 7,394 km<U+00B2> to 18,293 km<U+00B2> and the population rose from 1,333,800 (1980) to 2,198,000 (2000). By 1998, [[Tricity]] (greater Gda<U+0144>sk) constituted an absolute majority of the population; almost half of the inhabitants of the new region live in the centre.

== Education and science ==
[[Image:Danzig old.jpg|thumb|300px|Danzig in the 1890s.The ''Langer Markt'' street and City Hall]]

There are 14 universities with a total of 60,436 students, including 10,439  graduates [[as of 2001]].

* [[Gda<U+0144>sk University]] (Uniwersytet Gda<U+0144>ski)
* [[Gda<U+0144>sk University of Technology]] (Politechnika Gda<U+0144>ska)
* [[Medical Academy of Gdansk|Medical Academy]] (Akademia Medyczna)
* [[Physical Education Academy of Gdansk|Physical Education Academy]] (Akademia Wychowania Fizycznego im. J<U+0119>drzeja <U+015A>niadeckiego)
* [[Musical Academy of Gdansk|Musical Academy]] (Akademia Muzyczna im. Stanis<U+0142>awa Moniuszki)
* [[Arts Academy of Gdansk|Arts Academy]] (Akademia Sztuk Pi<U+0119>knych) [http://www.asp.gda.pl] 
* Instytut Budownictwa Wodnego PAN
* Ateneum <U+2014> Szko<U+0142>a Wy<U+017C>sza
* Gda<U+0144>ska Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Humanistyczna
* Gda<U+0144>ska Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Administracji
* Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Bankowa
* Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Spo<U+0142>eczno-Ekonomiczna
* Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Turystyki i Hotelarstwa w Gda<U+0144>sku
* Wy<U+017C>sza Szko<U+0142>a Zarz<U+0105>dzania

=== Scientific and regional organizations ===
* [[Gda<U+0144>sk Scientific Society]]
* [[Baltic Institute]] (Instytut Ba<U+0142>tycki), established [[1925]] in [[Toru<U+0144>]], since [[1946]] (?) in Gda<U+0144>sk
* TNOiK - Towarzystwo Naukowe Organizacji i Kierowania (Scientific Society for Organization and Management) O/Gda<U+0144>sk
* IBNGR - Instytut Bada<U+0144> nad Gospodark<U+0105> Rynkow<U+0105> (The Gda<U+0144>sk Institute for Market Economics) [http://www.ibngr.edu.pl/english/index2.htm]

